source_code.code:
public static void debug(boolean includeDate, String message) {
	if (includeDate) 
		message = new Date(System.currentTimeMillis()).toString() + " -
 "+ message; //$NON-NLS-1$
	System.out.println(message);
}

Bug.WithStack:
- add the following method to Policy. (copied from other Core Policy classes)
- convert all System.out.println debug statements to use this method

/**
 * Print a debug message to the console. If the given boolean is
 * <code>true</code> then pre-pend the message with the current date.
 */
public static void debug(boolean includeDate, String message) {
	if (includeDate) 
		message = new Date(System.currentTimeMillis()).toString() + " -
 "+ message; //$NON-NLS-1$
	System.out.println(message);
}
Released in HEAD

Bug.WithOutStack:
- add the following method to Policy. (copied from other Core Policy classes)
- convert all System.out.println debug statements to use this method

/**
 * Print a debug message to the console. If the given boolean is
 * <code>true</code> then pre-pend the message with the current date.
 */
public static void debug(boolean includeDate, String message) {
	if (includeDate) 
		message = new Date(System.currentTimeMillis()).toString() + " -
 "+ message; //$NON-NLS-1$
	System.out.println(message);
}
Released in HEAD

source_code.code:
public class TestLineBreakpoint {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    new Thread(new Runnable() {
      public void run() {
        while (1 == 1);
      }
    }).start();
    foo();  // <-- breakpoint here (suspend thread)
  }

  private static void foo() {
    System.out.println("test"); // <-- breakpoint here (suspend VM)
  }
}

Bug.WithStack:
1. Create the following compilation unit :

public class TestLineBreakpoint {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    new Thread(new Runnable() {
      public void run() {
        while (1 == 1);
      }
    }).start();
    foo();  // <-- breakpoint here (suspend thread)
  }

  private static void foo() {
    System.out.println("test"); // <-- breakpoint here (suspend VM)
  }
}

2. Add the two breakpoint, set 'suspend VM' for the second breakpoint.
3. Launch the program in debug mode.
4. When the first breakpoint is hit and the second thread is running, resume the
  first thread.
5. When the second breakpoint is hit (the VM is suspended), select the first
stack frame of the second thread.
A second instruction pointer is added.
6. Hit resume
